"about 1335–12 October 1372","1334–Female":"1334–Deceased","1335–1372":"1335–1372","1330–Male":"1330–Deceased","1358–1405":"1358–1405","1304–1357":"1304–1357","1308–Female":"1308–Deceased","1330":"1330","Abt 1358":"about 1358","1372":"1372","20 April 1357":"20 April 1357","12 October 1372":"12 October 1372","1304":"1304","1358":"1358","1357":"1357","1335":"1335","1334":"1334","Abt 1352":"about 1352","about 1335":"about 1335","1308":"1308","1405":"1405","Chaunte, Rougham, Suffolk, England":"Rougham, Suffolk, England, United Kingdom","Nettlestead, Suffolk, England, United Kingdom":"Nettlestead, Suffolk, England, United Kingdom","Aspall, Suffolk, England, United Kingdom":"Aspall, Suffolk, England, United Kingdom","Gwynedd, Wales":"Gwynedd, Wales, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Aspall","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English: habitational name from Aspull in Greater Manchester, named from Old English <i>æspe</i> ‘aspen’ + <i>hyll</i> ‘hill’. Compare   Asbell  .","Irish: in Ireland, this is usually the English name in 1 above imported, but according to MacLysaght it is also an east Leinster variant of   Archbold   (see   Archibald  )."],"variants":[{"name":"Asbell","meanings":["Altered form of English   Aspell  . Compare   Asbill  ,   Azbell  , and   Azbill  ."]}]},{"name":"Mary","type":"FIRST","meanings":["Hebrew: Bitter; Marion is the French form."],"variants":[{"name":"Marion","meanings":["Originally a medieval French diminutive form of   Marie  , introduced to Britain in the Middle Ages. In some places it was taken as a pet form of   Margaret   or   Margery .  As a male name, it is an altered form of the Continental male name <i>Marian</i>, a derivative of Latin <i>Marianus</i> (from   Marius  ), but is now rarely, if ever, used. It was the birth name of the American film star  John Wayne  (  1907–79 )."]},{"name":"Marcia","meanings":["Often used as a feminine equivalent of   Mark  , but in fact a feminine form of <i>Marcius</i>, itself a derivative of   Marcus .  One  St Marcia  is commemorated in a group with Felix, Luciolus, Fortunatus, and others; another with Zenais, Cyria, and Valeria; and a third with Ariston, Crescentian, Eutychian, Urban, Vitalis, Justus, Felicissimus, Felix, and Symphorosa. None is individually very famous."]}]},{"name":"de","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["‘Attainment’."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Mary de Aspall was born about 1335, in Aspall, Suffolk, England, United Kingdom, her father, John de Aspall, was 33 and her mother, Elizabeth, was 29. She married Sir Thomas de Naunton ,Knight about 1352. They were the parents of at least 1 daughter. She died on 12 October 1372, in Nettlestead, Suffolk, England, United Kingdom, at the age of 38."},"et":{"about 1335–12 October 1372":"umbes 1335–12. oktoober 1372","1334–Female":"1334–Surnud","1335–1372":"1335–1372","1330–Male":"1330–Surnud","1358–1405":"1358–1405","1304–1357":"1304–1357","1308–Female":"1308–Surnud","1330":"1330","Abt 1358":"umbes 1358","1372":"1372","20 April 1357":"20. aprill 1357","12 October 1372":"12. oktoober 1372","1304":"1304","1358":"1358","1357":"1357","1335":"1335","1334":"1334","Abt 1352":"umbes 1352","about 1335":"umbes 1335","1308":"1308","1405":"1405","Chaunte, Rougham, Suffolk, England":"Rougham, Suffolk, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Nettlestead, Suffolk, England, United Kingdom":"Nettlestead, Suffolk, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Aspall, Suffolk, England, United Kingdom":"Aspall, Suffolk, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Gwynedd, Wales":"Gwynedd, Wales, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"about 1335–12 October 1372":"noin 1335–12. lokakuuta 1372","1334–Female":"1334–Kuollut","1335–1372":"1335–1372","1330–Male":"1330–Kuollut","1358–1405":"1358–1405","1304–1357":"1304–1357","1308–Female":"1308–Kuollut","1330":"1330","Abt 1358":"noin 1358","1372":"1372","20 April 1357